<emphasis id="CEA6F437DFC86B9EE47A7FE2E8890486" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Polistes carolina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Linneaus, 1767) (as 
<taxonomicName id="AA264DCD9CD7D97D6F51BE03A59FF58A" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1836" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Polistes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polistes rubiginosus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubiginosus">
<emphasis id="75C663741EC7EC64CF5EFDB97F79EA5E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Polistes rubiginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lepeletier, 1836) (
<bibRefCitation id="9CB42D0CF6C8D58B770097A43209C351" author="Brues, CT" journalOrPublisher="Abteilung fuer Anatomie und Ontogenie der Tiere" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="241 - 270" refId="B11" refString="Brues, CT, 1903. A contribution to our knowledge of the Stylopidae. Zoologische Jahrbuecher. Abteilung fuer Anatomie und Ontogenie der Tiere 18: 241 - 270" title="A contribution to our knowledge of the Stylopidae. Zoologische Jahrbuecher." volume="18" year="1903">Brues 1903</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3E95B8E74B8731D1A4765EAE050D308D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3157/061.145.0202" author="Cook, JL" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="121 - 267" refId="B14" refString="Cook, JL, 2019. Annotated catalog of the order Strepsiptera of the World. Transactions of the American Entomological Society 145: 121 - 267, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3157/061.145.0202" title="Annotated catalog of the order Strepsiptera of the World." url="https://doi.org/10.3157/061.145.0202" volume="145" year="2019">Cook 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="73402388A00A49FBCDAFAF937F5DFB48" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="1B496E2FB9F5F35E733B4BAFBEDA9CE9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="429266058E99A83EB70A170D2B187572" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
USA: Texas (
<bibRefCitation id="E87847D485218F4DBAC9CF35F3127CD1" author="Brues, CT" journalOrPublisher="Abteilung fuer Anatomie und Ontogenie der Tiere" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="241 - 270" refId="B11" refString="Brues, CT, 1903. A contribution to our knowledge of the Stylopidae. Zoologische Jahrbuecher. Abteilung fuer Anatomie und Ontogenie der Tiere 18: 241 - 270" title="A contribution to our knowledge of the Stylopidae. Zoologische Jahrbuecher." volume="18" year="1903">Brues 1903</bibRefCitation>
), Georgia (
<bibRefCitation id="4FF98CE4B65F5B9B8E65A15F21E540FD" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2317/0022-8567-93.4.298" author="Garza, C" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="298 - 312" refId="B20" refString="Garza, C, Cook, JL, 2021. The taxonomy of adult females in the genus Xenos (Strepsiptera: Xenidae) with a re-description of the females of three North American species. Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society 93 (4): 298 - 312, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2317/0022-8567-93.4.298" title="The taxonomy of adult females in the genus Xenos (Strepsiptera: Xenidae) with a re-description of the females of three North American species." url="https://doi.org/10.2317/0022-8567-93.4.298" volume="93" year="2021">Garza and Cook 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="92BA4CC3F211C588D7D3AF7F7D884DF1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="D049811FB9B740369F8248E10EB1F3C4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="790C420191419A8BF71EB8512554DE71" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="89DA6BBF4DF5978244B940E60C3DEDBA" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1767" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Polistes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polistes carolina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carolina">
<emphasis id="E2A8C215FE316DD582750F09E9761A18" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Polistes carolina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Linneaus, 1767) was listed as a host by 
<bibRefCitation id="4C4630709D6F36B43C4AE78834240938" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3157/061.145.0202" author="Cook, JL" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="121 - 267" refId="B14" refString="Cook, JL, 2019. Annotated catalog of the order Strepsiptera of the World. Transactions of the American Entomological Society 145: 121 - 267, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3157/061.145.0202" title="Annotated catalog of the order Strepsiptera of the World." url="https://doi.org/10.3157/061.145.0202" volume="145" year="2019">Cook (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, because it was a former synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="85D5608FD22BB1F6325A01E721340BF5" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1836" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Polistes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polistes rubiginosus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubiginosus">
<emphasis id="B0BA536BFDE2785A17775788A948AA12" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Polistes rubiginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lepeletier, 1836, which does not occur in the USA. 
<bibRefCitation id="AE81B4CCDA930F7006969A068B015CBD" author="Kinzelbach, R" journalOrPublisher="Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B54" refString="Kinzelbach, R, 1971b. Morphologische Befunde an Faecherflueglern und ihre phylogenetische Bedeutung (Insecta: Strepsiptera). Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart" title="Morphologische Befunde an Faecherflueglern und ihre phylogenetische Bedeutung (Insecta: Strepsiptera)." year="1971 b">Kinzelbach (1971b)</bibRefCitation>
incorrectly stated Argentina as a location.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
